06/03/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Ten deputies of the ruling party National Movement Simeon II (NMS II) submitted registration documents on Wednesday (5 March) and set up a new parliamentary group called National Ideal for Unity. The new caucus issued a declaration calling for "consistency and transparency" in the government's position on Iraq and co-operation with the UN Security Council. Members also announced their intention to work for an all-party consensus on interior policy issues. NMS II said it would issue a response on Friday. (Sega, Standart, Monitor, Trud, 24 Hours - 06/03/03, Novinite, BTA - 05/03/03)
